</div>

<div class="article-body">

<p><strong>Bitcoin dominance just hit 55.99%</strong> ” the highest level in months ” while Bitcoin itself trades at <strong>$66,700, down -5.64% over 24 hours</strong>. This divergence is sending mixed signals across the crypto market, and how you read it could determine whether you catch the next altcoin season or get caught holding bags during a deeper risk-off rotation.</p>

<p>The question every trader is asking right now: <em>Is BTC.D at 56% a signal that altcoin season is approaching its trigger point, or is it a warning that capital is still fleeing altcoins for Bitcoin's relative safety?</em></p>

<p>The answer, as with most things in crypto, depends on context. But the historical data gives us a strong edge ” and right now, it favors the patient accumulator.</p>

<div class="data-box">
<h3>�œŠ Current Market Snapshot (June 3, 9:39 AM ICT)</h3>
